      THOMAS PARTRIDGE
 (Detective JE
). I took the prisoner into custody on 19th April on a warrant—I told him "I have a warrant for your arrest for obtaining 47l. 10s. from a gentleman of the name of Kirby, of Surrey Street, Strand, by means of a forged bill of acceptance;" he said "I gave the bill to a man named Ashton to take to my father to sign; he brought it back, and said it was all right, that my father had accepted it, and I did not know there was anything wrong "—I said "Do you know where the man Ashton is now?" he said "I believe he is dead "—I have inquired; his father told me he had been dead two years.

MESSRS. BIRON, MONTAGU WILLIAMS, SNAGG, and 
G. L. DENMAN 
Prosecuted;

MESSRS. POLAND, MONTAGU WILLIAMS, and 
CHARLES MATHEWS 
Prosecuted;

MR. DRUMMOND,
for the prosecution, offered no evidence against SALES.—NOT GUILTY . At the request of MR. FRITH, for STEWARD,
the Jury was discharged from giving a verdict, and the ease against him was postponed to the next Session.

MR. RAVEN 
